==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kitchenette
<hw>Kitch`en*ette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Kitchen</ets> + <ets>-ette</ets>.]</ety> <def>A room
combining a very small kitchen and a pantry, with the kitchen
conveniences compactly arranged, sometimes so that they fold up out of
sight and allow the kitchen to be made a part of the adjoining room by
opening folding doors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kitchenmaid</ent>⟦br⟧
